<plot>Sheridan Ridley-Smith, the world renowned director, has received divine inspiration for a blockbuster film, "Grits". It is an exploration of the human condition on a global scale. With big studio backing and an even bigger budget, "GRITS" is destined to become a masterpiece. Now all that's needed is a cast, a crew, someone to keep people from killing one another, a less ambitious ing√©nue;well, you get the point. Intercut with scenes from the actual film "Grits", "The Making of: GRITS" pulls back the covers on movie making and shows you how stars are found, the pleasures of the rehearsal process and what inspires the great scenes and masterful special effects.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?574353</url></doc>
